The article condemns the recent terrorist attack on the residence of Iraqi Prime Minister al-Kadhimi. It expresses relief that the Prime Minister was not injured and commends his leadership in calling for calm, restraint, and dialogue to protect the institutions of the state. The article emphasizes the need to hold the perpetrators accountable and strongly condemns violence aimed at undermining Iraq's democratic process. The United States has offered assistance to Iraq's security forces in investigating the attack and identifying those responsible. The article reaffirms the United States' support for Iraq's government and people in upholding their sovereignty and independence.